r Kiya]]'' \u2013 6/12\n*''[[Parinda]]'' \u2013 5/6\n*''[[Ram Lakhan]]'' \u2013 3/8\n*''[[ChaalBaaz|Chaalbaaz]]'' \u2013 2/3\n*''[[Tridev]]'' \u2013 2/5\n\n==References==\nhttps://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000245/1990/\n\n==See also==\n* [[37th Filmfare Awards]]\n* [[36th Filmfare Awards]]\n* [[Filmfare Awards]]\n\n{{Filmfare Awards}}\n\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards]]\n[[Category:1990 Indian film awards|Filmfare]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number = 35\n| award = Filmfare Awards\n| image = \n| caption = \n| date = 1990\n| site = \n| host = \n| producer = \n| director = \n| best_film = ''[[Maine Pyaar Kiya]]''\n| best_critic = ''[[Khayal Gatha]]''\n| most_wins = ''[[Maine Pyaar Kiya]]'' (6)\n| most_nominations = ''[[Maine Pyaar Kiya]]'' (12)\n| network = \n| duration = \n| ratings = \n| last = 34th\n| next = 36th\n}}\n\nThe '''35th Filmfare Awards''' were held in 1990. [[Sooraj Barjatya]]'s [[Maine Pyaar Kiya]] was named the Best Film of the year. [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]]'s [[Parinda]] was the other big winner on the night. This rivalry between [[Sooraj Barjatya]] and [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]] resurfaced in the [[40th Filmfare Awards]], where once again [[Sooraj Barjatya]]'s [[Hum Aapke Hain Kaun]] beat out [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]]'s [[1942 A Love Story]] for Best Film.\n\n==Main awards==\n[[File:Vidhu Vinod Chopra March 2015.jpg|alt=|thumb|197x197px|[[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]] \u2014 Best Director winner for [[Parinda]]]]\n[[File:JackieShroff.jpg|alt=|thumb|189x189px|[[Jackie Shroff]] \u2014 Best Actor winner for [[Parinda]]]]\n[[File:Sridevi.jpg|alt=|thumb|198x198px|[[Sridevi]] \u2014 Best Actress winner for [[ChaalBaaz]]]]\n[[File:Nana Patekar (Image 2), at IFFI Goa, 2017.jpg|alt=|thumb|149x149px|[[Nana Patekar]] \u2014 Best Supporting Actor winner for [[Parinda]]]]\n[[File:Rakhee Gulzar.jpg|alt=|thumb|149x149px|[[Raakhee]] \u2014 Best Supporting Actress winner for [[Ram Lakhan]]]]\n{| cla